data.title: Coronavirus JobKeeper package passes Parliament after Labor amendments fail
data.content:
Up to 6 million Australians are set to benefit from a $1,500 per fortnight wage subsidy, after Federal Parliament approved the Government’s $130 billion JobKeeper legislation.，Payments will be made to employers for up to six months during the coronavirus fuelled economic downturn, starting from next month. It is the single largest piece of government spending in Australian history, and more than 730,000 businesses have already registered with the Australian Taxation Office (ATO) for access to the scheme.
